included.title: User Experience Researcher - Accessibility

included.description: User Experience Researcher working with designers, product managers, developers, and prototypers to increase compliance with WCAG 2.0 guidelines and improve experiences for users with disabilities. Provides training and expert assistance to expand access to online education products through identification of problems, and application of research methods to reveal accessibility barriers.
included.title: User Experience Researcher - Accessibility

included.description:
Researched, wrote, and edited content in collaboration with subject experts for multiple customer facing online courses. Managed project timelines and coordinated resource needs with fellow researchers. Developed marketing plans for increased online course enrollment via Google Analytics.

Accomplishments
- Developed customer facing trainings, manuals, videos and comprehensive examinations for over 300 students.
- Generated product wireframes and mock-ups for testing which scored highly against recognized accessibility and usability metrics.
- Executed cognitive walkthroughs of users with disabilities to identify specific user needs and disability barriers.
- Conducted assessment of technology platforms according to design needs that were instrumental in influencing the overall scope and direction of 3 long term research projects.
included.title: Project Coordinator II

included.description:
Principle Investigator, Co-Principle Investigator (Co-PI) or Project Manager for federally funded grants and subcontracts currently in progress. Responsible for personnel management, subcontract oversight, online course development, research publication, delivery of information and technical assistance, and federal grant proposal writing.

Accomplishments
- Currently leading $2 million in federal and state-sponsored grants with multidisciplinary teams of up to 15 engineers, data scientists, and disability researchers.
- Co-Principal Investigator for a National Science Foundation collaborative assessing the effectiveness of virtual worlds for remote mentorship of students with disabilities.
- Performed market research and competitive analysis to assess new research opportunities.
- Conducted interviews and cognitive walkthroughs to improve University System of Georgia courseware through data-informed analysis.
- Developed and teach a graduate-level course on Usability, Accessibility, and Universal Design at Georgia Tech where students learn user testing methods on live websites.
- Designed surveys, heuristic evaluations and testing for virtual home modification software.
- Published results through HCI International, Accessing Higher Ground, and CSUN Annual Technology and Persons with Disabilities Conference.
included.title: Research Scientist I / II

included.summary:
10 years of applied and experimental research experience in progressively senior roles as qualitative UX researcher, accessibility specialist, and instructional designer. Designed and conducted experimental protocols using multiple UX research methods to generate actionable feedback from  students with disabilities in online & virtual world environments. 

Key expertise: ADA / Section 508 accessibility, applied research, survey development, data analytics, UX research methods, personnel management, grant writing, and project reporting.
